Volunteer & Intern Abroad Projects for All Ages

 
 International service projects for all ages Anyone (16+)   
Our standard Volunteer Abroad projects are for anyone 16 and older to undertake valuable service work to benefit the communities in which we work. Almost all of our standard projects do not have any requirements and are suitable for anyone who wants to give back by volunteering abroad. Available throughout the year, you can start anytime and choose your duration.
Learn More



Care 
Care volunteers work in orphanages, care centers, kindergartens, and special needs clinics around the world. You will help children get ready in the morning, play games, assist with homework and mealtimes, etc. These are very well-rounded volunteer placements that allow you to bring your own interests and passions in to share with the children.

 
Teaching 
Teaching volunteers work alongside local teachers in any of the destinations where we work. You do not need to have previous experience, just energy, enthusiasm, and patience. You can teach English to students or adults, and if you have the necessary skills you could also volunteer to teach French, IT, music, or sports.

 
Conservation & Environment 
Conservation and Environment projects focus on preserving some of the most beautiful and vulnerable ecosystems around the world. Whether you are volunteering in a rainforest, on the coast, or in a nature reserve, you will be working alongside our dedicated local staff to protect the area and raise awareness about the importance of conservation.



Sports 
Sports volunteer programs are popular with those who have a background in playing or coaching soccer, basketball, volleyball, water sports and more. Sports bring people together and help build strong communities, as well as contribute to the creation of healthy, happy individuals.

 
Archaeology 
Archaeology placements allow volunteers to explore an exciting new culture through history. You can also gain valuable, first-hand experience in the field of international archaeology. These placements do not require any previous experience or field work. Take a step back in time while working on Roman ruins in Romania or walk the trails of the Inca Empire in Peru.

 
Building 
Building volunteer placements involve some of the most important work needed in developing communities, including setting up basic infrastructure. Volunteering to building schools, libraries, and homes lays a foundation that supports locals even after your volunteer work abroad has ended.



Farming 
Farming volunteers get their hands dirty helping schools and communities raise crops to support themselves. Farming volunteers also have an important role to play promoting responsible and sustainable farming practices in the communities in which they are working.

 
Creative & Performing Arts 
Creative & Performing Arts placements are great for those who have a background in music, dance or drama and a passion for sharing their skills with another community. Volunteers impart their knowledge about their art form while learning the local traditions in their destination country.



View Options

 
 Gain professional experience abroad in a worthwhile field Anyone (16+)   
Our standard Intern Abroad projects are for anyone 16 or older to develop skills in a particular field. Volunteers work alongside local professionals in the role of an intern and help as needed. While the majority of standard projects do not have experience requirements, you should have a strong interest in the field in which you are working. Available throughout the year, you can start anytime and choose your duration.
Learn More



Medicine & Healthcare 
Medicine & Healthcare interns learn alongside doctors and other healthcare professionals in local hospitals or clinics in a developing country. You can choose to focus on a number of different areas including Medicine, Nursing, Midwifery, Dentistry, Public Health, Physical Therapy, Occupational Therapy, Speech Therapy, and Nutrition.

 
Medical School Electives 
Choose to do your elective placement overseas. Medical, dentistry, nursing, midwifery, physical therapy and occupational therapy electives are available. Placements are tailored to meet your needs.

 
Law & Human Rights 
Interning abroad on a Law and Human Rights placement provides interns with the opportunity to gain more in-depth knowledge of the human rights abuses that occur around the world, take an active role on campaigns and legislation to raise awareness, and work closely with community leaders and human rights lawyers to eliminate these abuses.



Journalism 
International interns on a Journalism program learn directly from experienced journalists how to further their own writing and reporting skills. Volunteers who intern abroad on a Journalism project work at a range of print and broadcast placements including newspapers, magazines, as well as radio and TV stations.

 
Microfinance 
These projects aim to assist local entrepreneurs in starting their own businesses and building sustainable futures for themselves and their communities.

 
International Development 
International Development interns work at development organizations and public offices abroad. Interns can become directly involved in community-based efforts to provide career opportunities to vulnerable populations, back small loan projects, and further disaster management planning.



Business 
Those interested in Business gain experience in various fields including accounting, marketing, human resources, public relations, and more. Interns gain skills, knowledge and experience essential to their future career.

 
Veterinary Medicine & Animal Care 
By interning abroad on a Veterinary Medicine & Animal Care placement, volunteers further their interests or studies in the animal care field. Interns gain knowledge about veterinary care and the treatment of local animal populations.

 
Internships for Social Work Students 
Intern abroad in the field of social work and gain practical experience and skills that you can use toward your degree. You will work alongside professionals in care facilities and schools.



View Options
Just for teens

 
 Group service trips for high school students Teens (16-19)   
High Schools Specials are for teens (16-19 years old) to join a group of their peers participating in worthwhile service and professional development projects under the constant supervision of Projects Abroad staff. These projects have set dates for 2-week and 4-week periods and follow a busy daily schedule, including guided tourism trips and cultural activities.
Learn More

Learn More
Just for Gap Years

 
 Gap year program in 5 countries for 8 months Gap Year (18-19)   
Global Gap is for students taking a gap year between high school and college and want to spend the year traveling around the world doing volunteer work. The program is designed for 5-15 students to go to 5 countries and participate in a wide variety of service and internship projects together. Global Gap starts in the fall and runs for 8 months, including returning home for a winter break.
Learn More

Learn More
Just for University Students

 
 Alternative Spring Break volunteer trips for university students University Age (18-22)   
The Alternative Spring Break Trips are short programs for college students to volunteer abroad together over spring break. These projects are scheduled for 1-week periods in February and March in some of our closest destinations.
Learn More



Jamaica 
Building As a volunteer in Jamaica, you will Work alongside an experienced local builder and help replace dangerous pit latrines with safer and cleaner modern toilets in schools. No construction experience is required. Sunday March 11th 2018 - Saturday March 17th 2018

 
Belize 
Care  Help provide care and educational support to underprivileged children in care centers and kindergartens in Belize. These placements have limited resources and local staff welcome an extra pair of helping hands. Sunday March 4th 2018 - Saturday March 10th 2018Sunday March 11th 2018 - Saturday March 17th 2018Sunday March 18th 2018 - Saturday March 24th 2018

 
Costa Rica 
Care  Work at a local care center for children in the town of Heredia, near San Jose. You will have plenty of opportunity to plan activities for the kids, so creativity is encouraged. This project is great if you want to learn Spanish or improve the skills you have. Sunday March 4th 2018 - Saturday March 10th 2018Sunday March 11th 2018 - Saturday March 17th 2018Sunday March 18th 2018 - Saturday March 24th 2018



Fiji 
Care  Help support children at a kindergarten in Fiji by teaching basic literacy and numeracy, games, and songs, as well as doing activities like arts & crafts. Sunday March 11th 2018 - Saturday March 17th 2018

 
Jamaica 
Care  Be a positive role model and lend a hand at an orphanage or care center in Jamaica, assisting the staff care for the children and providing fun and educational activities for the kids Sunday March 4th 2018 - Saturday March 10th 2018Sunday March 11th 2018 - Saturday March 17th 2018



Mexico 
Conservation  Live at a camp on the Pacific coast of Mexico, near a small village called Tecoman in the state of Colima. Volunteers protect endangered Olive Ridley turtles and their nests from predators, development and poachers. Sunday February 18th 2018 - Saturday February 24th 2018Sunday February 25th 2018 - Saturday March 3rd 2018Sunday March 4th 2018 - Saturday March 10th 2018Sunday March 11th 2018 - Saturday March 17th 2018Sunday March 18th 2018 - Saturday March 24th 2018



Argentina 
Medicine  Gain valuable medical experience by interning at a hospital in Cordoba, where you will shadow local doctors and participate in workshops and outreaches. Sunday March 4th 2018 - Saturday March 10th 2018Sunday March 11th 2018 - Saturday March 17th 2018Sunday March 18th 2018 - Saturday March 24th 2018

 
Ghana 
