View Options
Just for Professionals

 
 Volunteering abroad for skilled professionals Professionals (30+)   
These projects are structured the same as our Volunteer Abroad and Intern Abroad programs, but where volunteers work in roles where there is a specific need for people with professional experience. Start dates and duration of these projects are flexible to fit your schedule.
Learn More



Archaeology 
Work alongside fellow professionals to build upon your knowledge and skills while contributing to on-going work at archaeological sites and helping to make new discoveries.

 
Business 
As a Professional Business volunteer, you may take on the role of a consultant or business advisor working with an NGO, micro-finance project or local entrepreneurs.

 
Care 
Depending on your background and experience you could join us as a social worker, psychologist or art therapist in several of our destinations around the world.



Journalism 
Volunteers with professional qualifications in journalism or film production can pass on their skills on one of our journalism options overseas.

 
Law & Human Rights 
As a qualified lawyer or human rights specialist you can help on a range of law and human rights related projects in Africa or Asia. Sharing your knowledge will assist the local staff.

 
Medicine & Healthcare 
Qualified medical professionals can work in a range of areas depending on your specialism including working as a doctor, nurse, physiotherapist, speech therapist or nutritionist.



Teaching 
Professional teachers are welcomed by many of our destinations around the world, to teach subjects such as English, math, science, PE and special needs classes.

 
Veterinary Medicine 
Qualified vets can help in clinics and assist with training staff and volunteers in the south Pacific or Latin America. Your skills and experience will be welcomed by the local staff.



View Options
Just for 50+

 
 Group service trips for volunteers over 50  
Grown-up Specials are for anyone 50 or older to join volunteers of their own age on organized service trips in developing countries across the world. These projects do not have any requirements and each project has set dates for 2-week periods.
Learn More

Learn More
Special Arrangements

 
 Explore new cultures and extraordinary lifestyles Anyone (16+)   
Culture & Community projects offer volunteers the chance to be closely involved with unique communities abroad. In most cases you will be fully immersed in their daily lives, living and working alongside them and learning about their culture. Flexible start dates and durations.
Learn More



Cambodia - Khmer Project  
Khmer Project  Explore the ancient civilizations and engaging culture of modern Cambodia on our Khmer Project. Learn some of the Khmer language, cooking and local crafts and visit the main sites of Phnom Penh and the magnificent temples at Angkor Wat.

 
Fiji - Community Village Project  
Community Village Project  Fully immerse yourself into the exciting culture of this beautiful island nation by living and violunteering in a traditional Fijian village. You will live with a Fijian host family and help with the day-to-day task of the village, including teaching, farming, cooking, basket weaving, mat making, and gardening.

 
Jamaica - Maroon Community Project  
Maroon Community Project  Live with a traditional Maroon community in Jamaica. The Jamaican Maroons were runaway slaves who fought the British during the 18th century. Working alongside members of the Maroon community will help with a wide variety of tasks from teaching reading to cultural preservation projects.



Mongolia - Nomad Project  
Nomad Project  Live and work on the Mongolian steppe with a Nomadic family. Riding horses and camels and collecting firewood are all part of daily life in the desert.

 
Morocco - Nomad Project  
Nomad Project  Join a Moroccan nomadic family living in the largest desert on the planet - the Sahara. You will get to help with the livestock, prepare meals, and retrieve water while learning about the nomadic culture and way of life.


South Africa - Community Township Project  
Community Township Project  Help build a community center in the township of Lavender Hill and contribute to various community projects, including nutrition and childcare.



Tanzania - Community Village Project  
Community Village Project  Experience a unique insight into the Maasai tribe's way of life, and play a vital role when it comes to helping the Maasai people.



View Options

 
 Winter break group trips for volunteers of all ages  Anyone (16+)   
Our Winter Break Trips are short-term volunteer programs for anyone ages 16 and older. These trips take place during the winter break on fixed dates in December and January. Volunteers can choose from 2-week and 4-week trips.
Learn More



Ghana
Care & Community Volunteer in Ghana and help make a difference in the lives of children in an orphanage or day care center. You will also contribute to valuable renovation activities in the community. Wednesday December 20th 2017 - Tuesday January 2nd 2018

 
