Ghana
Medicine  Experience different approaches to medicine and treatments in a developing country and give back through worthwhile outreach work in underprivileged communities. Wednesday December 20th 2017 - Tuesday January 2nd 2018



Nepal
General Building ProjectsVolunteer during your winter break and contribute to important disaster relief efforts in the wake of the devastating April 2015 earthquakes in Kathmandu, Nepal. Wednesday December 20th 2017 - Tuesday January 2nd 2018

 
Sri Lanka
Medicine  Gain valuable experience in the field of medicine in Sri Lanka over the winter break. Here, you will shadow local doctors at a busy general hospital and participate in outreach activities. Wednesday December 20th 2017 - Tuesday January 2nd 2018



View Options

 
 Foreign language training one-on-one Anyone (16+)   
We offer a variety of Language Courses that allow you to become part of the local community and learn about the culture while studying the language. You can choose to do a Language Course full-time, where you will receive 15 hours of one-on-one classes a week. These classes will be tailored to your ability and personal interests. You can also participate in classes that run alongside your main volunteer placement. If you choose this option, we offer 5-hour, 14-hour, 30-hour, and 60-hour courses.
Learn More

Learn More

 
CombinationsAnyone (16+)
There are many different programs you can do with us in a wide variety of destinations, so we've provided some ideas of combined projects and destinations you can choose from. You do not have to do the suggested combinations- you can combine any projects or destinations as you would like!
Learn More

Learn More

 
 For schools, universities, and corporations  
Groups of 5 or more can participate in tailor-made group trips in any destination. Most projects can be customized to fit the goals of a group and the needs of the local communities in which we work.
Learn More

Learn More

 
 Bring your children on the family trip of a lifetime  
In most destinations children under 16 years old can accompany their parents on our projects to volunteer abroad together as a family.
